full_text: Having had a bit of a think, I wonder if world might be ready for the return of the longhand essay. If it isn't worth saying a thing properly, then is probably isn't worth saying.

full_text: I'm not completely sure what to do about it, to be honest, other than to withdraw. Nobody is going to listen to *my* voice, and if they do, the chances of them engaging in a reasoned discussion are minimal *before* you take into account the limitations of the platform.

full_text: Personally, I blame the influence of the wider media who have been wilfully misinterpreting material for at least a couple of centuries. If that has become the standard of our public discourse (particularly in America) then no wonder nobody remembers how to think properly.

This applies across the political spectrum.
